        public static boolean calculateFromArgs(java.lang.String[] args,
                                        double result)

        Performs the mathematical operation denoted by the third element of the args array on the first and second element and returns true if the result of the calculation rounded down to its nearest neighbouring integer is equal to the second method parameter or false otherwise. ((This is a method of JavadocEx)) ((This is just a link to another method: main(java.lang.String[]). But this link can be shortened: main(java.lang.String[])))

        Parameters:
        args - array of arguments
        result - awaited result after the operation is performed
        Returns:
        the logical boolean value of the equity check between the input and the desired result
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if there aren't exactly 3 arguments provided
        java.lang.ArithmeticException - if there is an attempt of dividing by zero
